    'qui.intro': '<strong>Born in the neighbourhoods of Badalona.</strong> Built on basketball, street culture and values. We believe basketball is a right, not a privilege. We catalogue courts, report their condition and drive projects that transform lives. Because we want everyone — regardless of their physical, intellectual or economic circumstances — to enjoy basketball with dignity and joy. No exceptions.',
    'mvv.m.title': 'Mission', 'mvv.v.title': 'Vision', 'mvv.val.title': 'Values',
    'mvv.m.text': 'To recover and care for neighbourhood courts to foster a vibrant, creative and respectful street basketball culture where all ages play as equals. We work so that institutions take on maintenance and recognise the educational value of public space.',
    'mvv.v.text': 'A Badalona where urban courts are lively, well-maintained spaces woven into daily neighbourhood life — a city that leads street basketball and turns it into a symbol of shared identity.',
    'mvv.val.text': 'Basketball without economic, social or physical barriers. Open, free and accessible courts for everyone: with ramps, adapted spaces and doors open to all abilities. An intergenerational, inclusive meeting point where every person has their place on the court.',
    'act.eyebrow': 'Activities & projects', 'act.h2a': 'What we', 'act.h2b': 'do …',
    'act.intro': 'Court renovations, exhibitions, recognition events, round tables and direct action to put street basketball at the heart of the city.',
