    'aito.eyebrow': 'Exclusive interview',
    'aito.cred': 'Basketball coach · Over 50 years of experience · Beijing 2008 Olympics',
    'aito.lead': 'We talk to one of the most influential coaches in the history of Spanish basketball. Aíto shares his thoughts on talent, mistakes, coaching and why basketball is much more than a scoreboard. Interview by <strong style="color:rgba(255,255,255,.85)">Ramon Gargallo</strong>.',
    'aito.format.lbl': 'Format', 'aito.format.val': 'Written interview',
    'aito.preguntes.lbl': 'Questions', 'aito.preguntes.val': '20 questions',
    'aito.btn.llegir': 'Read the interview ↓', 'aito.btn.tancar': 'Close the interview ↑',
    'aito.btn.pdf': 'Download PDF ↗',
    'aito.tag1': 'References', 'aito.tag2': 'Basketball', 'aito.tag3': 'Coaching', 'aito.tag4': 'Values',
    'villacampa.eyebrow': 'Interview · First JAB · Archive',
    'villacampa.cred': 'Player and President of Club Joventut Badalona · 40 years linked to the club · Legend of Catalan basketball',
    'villacampa.lead': 'Jordi Villacampa is a landmark figure in Badalona, both as a player and as president of the club that bears the city\'s name. For forty years he was connected to Joventut. He was admired by many, a fixture on school folders, and above all has won hearts with the way he carries himself.',
    'villacampa.format.val': 'Written interview', 'villacampa.preguntes.val': '4 questions',
    'villacampa.btn.llegir': 'Read the interview ↓',
    'villacampa.tag1': 'Legend', 'villacampa.tag2': 'Joventut', 'villacampa.tag3': 'Badalona', 'villacampa.tag4': 'Street courts',
    'aito.q01': 'If you closed your eyes and thought about basketball 40 years ago, what feelings come to mind?',
    'aito.q02': 'What do you think basketball has gained and lost over the years?',
    'aito.q03': 'Do you feel today\'s training is too focused on winning and not enough on learning?',
    'aito.q04': 'What did street basketball give young players that academies sometimes lack today?',
    'aito.q05': 'Do you remember a moment when a young player surprised you with something off the script?',
    'aito.q06': 'What is the difference between a good player and a truly special one?',
    'aito.q07': 'How do you feel when you see so many of your former players now working as coaches?',
    'aito.q08': 'What would you say to a young player today who is afraid of making mistakes on the court?',
    'aito.q09': 'Has your understanding of leadership changed over the years?',
    'aito.q10': 'When you coach or watch a game, what is the first thing you look at?',
    'aito.q11': 'In an era of data analysis and video, does it worry you that the game might lose spontaneity?',
    'aito.q12': 'Which game or period do you remember most fondly, beyond just the result?',
    'aito.q13': 'When a player fully trusts you, how does that change the way you coach them?',
    'aito.q14': 'How do you see the relationship between clubs and youth academies today?',
    'aito.q15': 'What drove you to innovate, even knowing you would face criticism?',
    'aito.q16': 'What does it mean to you to develop players, beyond teaching them basketball?',
    'aito.q17': 'Is there a piece of advice you have kept unchanged since your early years as a coach?',
    'aito.q18': 'What inspires you to stay connected to basketball after so many achievements?',
    'aito.q19': 'When you look at today\'s generation of coaches, do you notice your influence?',
    'aito.q20': 'If you had to give a final message to kids just starting out, what would it be?',
    'busquets.eyebrow': 'Interview · June 2025',
    'busquets.cred': 'Youth basketball coach · Over 20 years of experience · Badalona',
    'busquets.lead': 'We talk with a coach who has dedicated more than twenty years to shaping people through basketball in Badalona. David reflects on the invisible work of coaches, the essential role of families, and why a scoreboard lasts a day while values last a lifetime.',
    'busquets.format.val': 'Written interview', 'busquets.preguntes.val': '18 questions',
    'busquets.btn.llegir': 'Read the interview ↓',
    'busquets.tag1': 'Coaching', 'busquets.tag2': 'Values', 'busquets.tag3': 'Badalona', 'busquets.tag4': 'Coaches',
    'busquets.q01': 'After more than twenty years coaching, what does basketball in Badalona mean to you?',
    'busquets.q02': 'Badalona is still the cradle of basketball. Does it still maintain that identity?',
    'busquets.q03': 'What is the main challenge in youth basketball?',
    'busquets.q04': 'Is the result prioritised too much?',
    'busquets.q05': 'What values does basketball transmit?',
    'busquets.q06': 'Do coaches receive the recognition they deserve?',
    'busquets.q07': 'Is the financial compensation enough?',
    'busquets.q08': 'What should change?',
    'busquets.q09': 'Why is it hard to find coaches?',
    'busquets.q10': 'Do clubs give enough support?',
    'busquets.q11': 'Is an emotional support figure needed?',
    'busquets.q12': 'What is resilience?',
    'busquets.q13': 'Do we educate in failure?',
